summary: honestly, when you see either ariana's dangerous woman docuseries, taylor's reputation stadium tour, or any beyoncé's...
body: honestly, when you see either ariana’s dangerous woman docuseries, taylor’s reputation stadium tour, or any beyoncé’s performance, you really realise how wide the gap between male and female performance standards goes…….. the artists i just mentionned go to extreme lengths to offer both a visual and vocal show to whoever buys tickets to see them, they deliver on special effects, fierce looking but usually demanding stage outfits (imagine just the pain from the heels!), !!!choreos!!!, their concerts are like the whole package. and when you compare it to a shawn mendes, ed sheeran, harry styles or a lot of male performer’s show, it’s blatantly painful to see the difference : absolutely no hate towards them (i love them!!), but male artists get to just grab their guitar and microphone, throw some light effects in the mix, wear comfortable clothes and shoes, and NO ONE IS SHOOKED, and i just hate these double standards. imo that’s just yet another reflection of how women are expected to do so?? much?? more?? all the time. anyway, all i’m saying is i wish that female artists could design tours where it’s just them in tshirt and jeans, with their guitar, and still be recognised as the artists that they are, and that male artists would sometimes step up, or feel free to step up their game

summary: yesterday I completed three long years at university and earned myself a bachelors degree! Honestly university was a struggle...
body:
TAYLOR! I FINALLY GRADUATED 🎓🦋✨

yesterday I completed three long years at university and earned myself a bachelors degree! Honestly university was a struggle for me at times and I really felt like giving up on some occasions, this last year was especially hard but if i’m honest one of the only things that got me through it was you.

Towards the end of my first semester I got to hug you and thank you for everything and that motivated me enough to keep pushing and working hard all year. At the end of my second semester I got to see you on tour, which was a MUCH needed stress relief and reward for all the hard work i’d been putting into my work. At the start of the year i told you how much the lyrics “nothing safe is worth the drive” meant to me and honestly those lyrics have pushed me and motivated me to get where I am today. I knew if I wanted to do something worthwhile i’d have to take a chance on myself and also take risks and that’s exactly what i did!

Thankyou for always being a constant source of strength and happiness for me. thankyou for getting me through these last three years (and all the previous ones in my life). At this point i’m absolutely terrified for the future and don’t really have a direction. People do keep asking me and i have no answers and while that scares me i’m trying to stay hopeful (if you have any advice that’d be greatly appreciated). I feel pressure to have my whole life figured out right now but I really just don’t. Either way, I know what I have achieved is something i’m proud of and I also know I couldn’t have done it without you.

I love you and I hope you’re proud ❤️❤️❤️
